<h3 class="date"><a href="/2011/jul/27/">&#x27a0;</a> July 27, 2011</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="cost-false-positives-laughing-" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://laughingmeme.org/2011/07/23/cost-of-false-positives/">Cost of false positives - Laughing Meme</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>Lovely post from Kellan explaining why Twitter (and other sites) can&#8217;t &#8220;just block all the spammers&#8221;.</p>

<p>When your best users and your worst users share common outlying behaviour, things get tough.</p>

